In .NET 10 (and Android API 30+), `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` is deprecated at the platform level. Here's what to do instead:

## Option 1: Use `adjustResize` in the manifest (still works)

In `Platforms/Android/AndroidManifest.xml`, set on your `<activity>`:

```xml
android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize"
```

This still functions but is formally deprecated.

## Option 2 (Recommended): Handle keyboard insets via padding

In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        var rootView = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Apply bottom padding equal to keyboard height (minus nav bar)
            var bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom - navInsets.Bottom, 0);
            v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

## Layout tip for chat screens

Use a `Grid` so the input bar naturally stays at the bottom and the message list shrinks when padding is applied:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" />
    <Entry Grid.Row="1" Placeholder="Type a message..." />
</Grid>
```

The insets approach is the modern replacement—it uses the `WindowInsetsCompat` API that Google recommends for edge-to-edge apps going forward.
